name: In The Field Photo Workshops Seattle
description: Your pro-photographer/instructor, photographing Seattle for decades, will take you and a maximum of 11 other people, to unforgettable places that you may not even know existed. With advice on photographing, you develop the art form and simultaneously see wondrous sites found only in Seattle. Monthly locales vary to learn new lessons in each workshop, year-round while an instructor shares knowledge for photographing it. Beginner & advanced, have been enjoying our workshops for over 13 years. Advanced shooters begin with the in-the-field of a photogenic locale but for beginners, there is a pre-session sit-down learn your camera controls. Everyone together, but with enough autonomy to allow each to capture what they see, the instructor tending to each participant.

review.name: Flytographer for the win
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful time with Coty in Seattle as our daughters senior photos shot. We chose to do a different path than the in a meadow gazing to no where! We did a down town urban feel to match her future dreams of moving to the East Coast on the coast and live in the big city!! Coty worked her magic to bring out our shy girl and got some wonderful shots! Thank you Coty in Seattle and  Flytographer.

review.name: Wonderful experience with Kelly in Seattle for Flytographer
review.reviewBody: Our photo session with Kelly was wonderful! My mom and I live on opposite coasts and met in Seattle for a mom/daughter getaway. We don't get to see each other often, and I can't remember the last time we went away, just the two of us, nor when we last had professional photos taken. So I surprised my mom with the Flytographer session as a momento from our trip. We tend to be awkward people when it comes to photos - we'll inevitably stand in the exact wrong way so we end up looking like the  widest, weirdest versions of ourselves! But Kelly made us feel at ease and gave great guidance for positioning; and the photos turned out lovely and have a casual, easy-breezy feeling (a far cry from our usual stiff and forced demeanor in all other photos!). I can't say enough good things about Kelly, who was so kind and patient during our session, and I am so grateful for the beautiful photos she captured for me and my mom! I definitely plan to book other Flytographer sessions on future vacations around the globe!

itemListElement.name: Food Tasting & Arts Tour of Pike Place Market

name: Food Tasting & Arts Tour of Pike Place Market
description:
This tour is a treat for all senses. First and foremost, we'll try some of the delicious treats only available at Pike Place Market! We will also learn about the history of the Market and view much of the incredible art on display. We'll also take the time to be serenaded by one of the many street performers. Walking through the fascinating labyrinth of the Pike Place is a special treat. Take in breath taking views of Elliot Bay and the surrounding mountains (weather permitting!) and enjoy special attention from your guide due to small group sizes. 
Wander Northwest Walking Tours is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate tours in the Pike Place Market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: Amazing tour guide, had a wonderful time
review.reviewBody: The tour guide was absolutely amazing, he packed up food during the tour for my girlfriends mother when she couldnt come with us.

review.name: BEST way to see the market - on foot with this guide
review.reviewBody: This was really interesting. I did not know much about the market and our guide, James was super knowledgeable about the history and maybe even more importantly, all the best food sites. He actually gave us some samples along the way and pointed out all kinds of quirky elements of this amazing market. Saw the iconic Starbucks, left some gum on the wall, payed homage to a pair of musical performing cats, sampled some other-wordly smoked salmon... The pace was excellent and he tailored his remarks for our family really well (including kids). Definitely recommend.

review.name: Seattle must do experience
review.reviewBody: This tour was a joy! James did a wonderful job of presenting the market in its full glory, with a perfect balance of history and present sights, tastes, and smells. I grow up in the region but hadn't known all the amazing background and growth of the Public Market over many years. Thanks!

review.name: Fun & tasty!
review.reviewBody: Great tour! I learned a lot about Seattle. My friends and I had a blast eating our way through the market. James was an entertaining and considerate guide.

name: Queen Anne True Crime Tour
description: This is a scenic tour traveling through historical neighborhoods with some true crime featured as well. It is an unique way to see Seattle and hear about Seattle's interesting past. It combines sightseeing along with some dark history of the city.

review.name: Seattle true crime tour
review.reviewBody: Jake was an excellent tour guide and shared a lot of new information with us. She also shared quite a bit of Seattle history in the tour. I would recommend it.

review.name: An Entertaining and Educational Tour for Locals and Visitors Alike
review.reviewBody: Our senior center group took a ghost tour by van with Private Eye on Seattle Tours. It was well worth the price of admission. Jake is a great storyteller and just as good of a driver. (Seriously, her ability to concentrate on everything the city streets had to throw at us AND continue to tell us about the locations we were viewing was practically supernatural.) Everyone in the group currently lives in Seattle, and she had stories and spooky facts that people didn't already know. So, locals, this tour is good for you and the out-of-towners. You get to see a lot of the city, including several spots that tourists don't usually get to see. Overall, the feedback from people in our group was quite enthusiastic and uniformly positive, which is definitely not always the case. I will be planning on taking her True Crime tour at some point, as I'm sure it's also quite good. Book this if you're considering it. You won't be disappointed.

review.name: Crime History
review.reviewBody: We had a great time on this tour. Interesting true crime stories and points of interest. My only wish was we got to get out and stop more but I dont think that could happen on this type of tour. Our guide was so nice and informative. Went above and beyond.

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Jake was wonderful. It was a great tour! Service was very personal and we would do this tour again!!

review.name: Thumbs up!
review.reviewBody: Jake was my guide on this tour and she was deeply knowledgeable, enthusiastic, and a great story teller. I highly recommend this tour!

review.name: A must do!
review.reviewBody:
Looked forward to the tour for the past couple of years, as I was meant to visit in 2020!

Jake has always been super responsive and and she was on time at the specified pick up location.

We had a wonderful day, she is so knowledgeable and goes out of her way to make sure you enjoy your tour and get all the photos you want.

For any music or true crime fans, this is a must. As we wouldn't have found these areas on our own.

review.name: Exellent tour
review.reviewBody:
Jake picked us up at our hotel and gave us much insight not only on the crimes and locations but also about Seattle.
We got to see places you wouldnt normally see riding a taxi or Uber.
Jake was the perfect tour guide, not only super nice but also funny.
Love this. We were so happy :)

review.name: True Crime Fun
review.reviewBody: I really enjoyed Jake and her stories of the city. I went by myself. Our group only had the three of us. I really appreciated that Jake picked us up at our hotel. That was very convenient. If you are a lover of true crime or just enjoy a little dark history, this is the tour for you.

Create a Ukulele: Say aloha to the happiest little instrument. You dont need to be musically inclined to play along! Paint your ukulele, put it together, then tune it up. Our Hosts guide you through the entire process, so youll leave with a fully functional ukulele thats as unique as a piece of art.

Yaymaker events give you everything you need to get up, get out, and get making! Instruction is provided by an expert host, so no experience is required, and everything you need is supplied. Grab your friends to paint, plant, tinker, and buildand give your week something to shout about.

Create a Ukulele events are partnered with local restaurants and bars. At the checkout page, simply enter your voucher code listed on your TripAdvisor confirmation email. Any remaining amount due is the experience fee for your event.

itemListElement.name: Olympic National Park Full-Day Tour W/ Scenic State Ferries

name: Olympic National Park Full-Day Tour W/ Scenic State Ferries
description:
Take the roundtrip Bainbridge Ferry to Puget Sound and embrace the beautiful coastline and island along the way!Be inspired by the glacier-capped peaks, valleys of forests, hot springs, and rugged Pacific coastline.Discover the magnificent Hurricane Ridge and spectacular Lake Crescent!Take in all the breathtaking scenic views along the journey.

04/01-10/15 Itinerary: 
Seattle takes the ferry go to Bainbridge (45 mins)  Olympic National Park  Hurricane Ridge (75 mins)  Lake Crescent (30 mins)  Marymere Falls (45 mins)  Bainbridge takes the ferry back to Seattle (45 mins)

10/16-03/31 Itinerary: 
Seattle  Olympic National Park  Lake Crescent (30 mins)  East Beach (30 mins)  Marymere Falls (45 mins)  Ediz Hook (30 mins)  Bainbridge takes the ferry back to Seattle (45 mins)

Explore the park's best spots by hiking or snowshoeing, depending on the season.

review.name: Wonderful experience good guide
review.reviewBody: Jeremy was very informative about the places we were visiting. He also made sure we reached back in time which, as he explained, is a tricky situation. He took care of all 12 tourist very well. For each place visited he told the expected time back and also the reason for that. Overall I had a wonerful experience.

review.name: Cannot Miss, great tour. Amazing Guide
review.reviewBody: great Itenrary, AMAZING tour guide. Very good natured, cooperative and helpful. Jereme contacted me a day earlier and gave me all the details and was available to answer any questions. The tour went smoothly and he explained each location very well. He brought a great energy to the tour.

review.name: Well-Organized and Informative Tour with Chris
review.reviewBody:
I recently took the Olympic National Park tour, and Chris did a great job guiding us through the experience. He kept everything running smoothly and made sure we stayed on schedule, which really helped us make the most of our time at each stop.

Chris shared interesting facts about the park and its diverse ecosystems, which added a lot of value to the trip. You could tell he was committed to giving us a thorough and enjoyable experience, and I appreciated how he made sure we were always informed about what to expect.

If youre looking for a well-structured tour with plenty of fascinating insights, this is a great choice. Thanks, Chris, for helping us explore such an amazing place!

review.name: Good time in the Washington state
review.reviewBody: The tour is so nice. Nan is a good tour guide who's knowledgeable about the location. Would 100% recommend this tour to everyone!
Miss Nan

review.name: Excellent trip with Nan
review.reviewBody: Nan was a wonderful tour guide. She was very friendly and helpful. She went out of her way to make sure we had a great experience.

review.name: Nan is the best guide! Olympic is beautiful and the trip is so worth it!
review.reviewBody: Nan was the best tour guide we could have hoped for! We had an amazing time and saw incredible views from mountains to forest. Nan was extremely kind and helpful, and she made sure we had a great time for our first visit to Olympic. I would highly recommend requesting her as your guide if you can. We saw many scenic overlooks and did one hike to an awesome waterfall upon her recommendation.

review.name: Snow Capped Mountains and Beautiful Horizons
review.reviewBody: Our tour of Olympic National Park was amazing thanks to our guide Jennifer. She was professional and friendly while also making sure we stayed on time. She took great photos of each party in our group at different viewpoints along the trail. She pointed out places of interest and gave us information about the places we visited. The weather was perfect at the beginning of May.

review.name: A great day out in Nature & Olympic National Park
review.reviewBody: A great day tour out to Olympic National Park from Seattle with a handy pickup/dropoff. I would recommend it for those looking for a great day in nature and the national park. The mountain views and waterfall visit are well worth the visit. The tour guide Jennifer was very hospitable and welcoming over the tour.

itemListElement.name: Mount Rainier National Park Day Tour from Seattle

name: Mount Rainier National Park Day Tour from Seattle
description: Mount Rainier, an iconic landmark in Washington, is the highest mountain in the Cascade Range and the state of Washington. Known for its glaciated peak, this active volcano spawns five major rivers and is surrounded by stunning natural beauty, including waterfalls, vast lakes, and lush forests. The Summer Itinerary (MayOctober) includes stops at Longmire Museum, Christine Falls, Narada Falls, Paradise Visitor Center, and Reflection Lake. The Winter Itinerary (NovemberApril) features Longmire Museum and Wonderland Trail, with adjustments made for heavy snowfall. This tour offers breathtaking views and unforgettable experiences year-round.

review.name: Great Tour at Mount Ranier
review.reviewBody: Our guide, Duan, was incredibly informative and made the whole trip enjoyable from start to finish. The drive was smooth and comfortable, and we appreciated how well everything was explainedfrom the history of the park to the different viewpoints and trail highlights. It was clear our guide knew the area well and had a real passion for sharing it. Definitely recommend this tour,

review.name: Great day for a tour
review.reviewBody: I booked this tour last minute as other plans fell through, and so glad I did. It was a good choice. Driver was on time, nice, and very knowledgeable about the sites and stops. He also did a nice job of explaining everything in English and Mandarin so everyone on the tour could follow and felt included. We made a stop beforehand at a local grocery store to grab lunch which we ate after the hike. It was a perfect day weather wise so we got amazingly clear views all day. The hike was good, some icy spots but fine with hiking boots and our guide had walking sticks for us to borrow as well. On the way back we stopped at an iron sculpture park which was also cool. All in all a great day and tour, especially if the weather is good.
9/22/2024JeremeJereme!

review.name: Great day at Mt Rainier National Park
review.reviewBody: Easy trip up to the mountain. Made stops at several important points in the park. Tour guide was knowledgeable and accommodating. Great day.

review.name: Perfect Day at Rainier!
review.reviewBody: Our trip to the mountains was amazing! Our tour guide Edmund was attentive, thoughtful and volunteered to take a lot of pictures. This tour covers all the amazing spots and is a perfect day spent   At Mt Rainier!

review.name: A very good day your
review.reviewBody: Our Guide, Edmund, was very kind, informative and helpful. The tour was overall amazing And we covered pretty much all the important places in the Mount Rainier national Park

review.name: Mount Rainier Tour
review.reviewBody: Jereme, our tour guide, was attentive, thoughtful, kind, and enthusiastic. We thoroughly enjoyed the tour despite the less-than-amazing weather. Not only that, but Jereme provided us with plenty of water. Additionally, he offered to take family photos of us. We would highly recommend Jereme for your tour!

review.name: Great trip highly recommend
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful time. The views were amazing and our tour guide Edmund was the best. He was knowledgeable on all the great photo spot!

review.name: Unsafe
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide/bus driver was not knowledgeable about the area or sites that we visited. She was nervous about driving in the fog claiming I dont think I can do this. Her driving in general was erratic and dangerous. To top the trip off, she started to text while driving on the highway as we got closer to Seattle.  My husband had to ask her to stop because we felt so unsafe.  Not worth $672.  Was expecting a knowledgeable guide with experience with driving in this national park.

review.name: Worth your time!

name: 2-Day Mount Rainier & Olympic National Parks Tour from Seattle
description:
Visit Olympic National Park and Mount Rainier National Park. Explore the unique combination of snow and volcanic landscape at Mount Rainier!Visit Olympic National Park and be inspired by the glacier-capped peaks, valleys of forests, hot springs, and rugged Pacific coastline.Take in all the breathtaking scenic views along the journey.

Room Details

One Room Selection

review.name: 2 nationals parks in 2 days....

itemListElement.name: Snoqualmie Falls and Leavenworth Day Tour from Seattle

name: Snoqualmie Falls and Leavenworth Day Tour from Seattle
description:
Discover Snoqualmie Falls and Leavenworth

Experience a perfect blend of natural beauty and Bavarian charm on this day trip.

Morning: Snoqualmie Falls
Visit the iconic Snoqualmie Falls, a breathtaking 268-foot waterfall featured in Twin Peaks. Capture stunning views and enjoy the serene surroundings.

Afternoon: Leavenworth
Explore Leavenworth, a Bavarian-style village known for its lively atmosphere, seasonal beauty, and rich history. Stroll through its charming streets, shop for unique European souvenirs, and savor authentic German cuisine and beer.

A must-do trip for nature lovers, history buffs, and food enthusiasts alike!

Itinerary:

Snoqualmie Falls (45 mins)  Leavenworth the German Village (180 mins)

review.name: one-day trip to the German town

This one-day trip to the German town (Leavenworth) from Seattle was amazing! Mark was friendly, and the schedule was relaxednot rushed at all. The town looked like a fairy tale, full of cute shops and beautiful buildings. We had delicious German sausages and desserts!

The weather was great, and we took lots of photos. There was free time to walk around and shop for souvenirs. A fun and relaxing dayI highly recommend it!

review.name: Seattle trip
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide was nan she Made sure we were comfortable and super sweet. The ride up was beautiful the scenery was breathtaking so beautiful.

review.name: March 2025
review.reviewBody:
I agree with other reviews that wrote how this is more transportation to the two sights. There is no "guided tour" of these sights. I booked this trip solo, so I did not mind paying to be driven to the sights. It would have been cheaper to get a rental car and tour by myself. 

The driver was a nice guy and the tour mostly ran on time. I was slightly annoyed that other passengers were late to the agreed upon departure time. This wasn't the driver's fault.

review.name: Snoqualmie Falls/Leavenworth
review.reviewBody:
We were sent reminders regarding the planned excursion. We were given precise pickup time and address .
We were told the scheduled drive time and time at Snoqualmie Falls.  We then had a relaxing, beautiful scenic drive to Leavenworth.  We got a few hours to shop , browse and eat before heading Back to our drop off place.  Chris was on time, safe driving and provided a snack and water. He also shared information regarding the 2 destinations.  A trip well worth the time.

name: Seattle,Space Needle, Pike Place Market&Gas Works Park 1-Day Tour
description:
Experience the best of Seattle on this 1-day city tour, showcasing its iconic landmarks and vibrant culture. Begin with a visit to Gas Works Park, followed by the bustling Pike Place Market, home to the original Starbucks. Enjoy optional stops at the Sky View Observatory for breathtaking views, the stunning Chihuly Glass Garden, and the captivating Museum of Flight. Along the way, admire the Space Needle from the outside, a true symbol of Seattle. This tour offers a seamless itinerary that captures the citys charm, history, and innovation in just one day.

Gas Works Park (30 mins)  Pike Place Market (120 mins, where first Starbucks located)  Sky View Observatory at Columbia Center (Optional, 60 mins)  Space Needle(Outside visit)  Chihuly Glass Garden (Optional, 75 mins)  The Museum of Flight (Optional, 120 mins)

review.name: Hidden fees
review.reviewBody:
Great tour, but felt misled about extra fees

This was our first time visiting Seattle, and with only three days to explore, my family and I wanted to make the most of our time. We booked this tour thinking it would be a great way to cover a lot in one dayand overall, it was! Our tour guide was friendly and knowledgeable, and even went above and beyond by taking us to see the cherry blossoms at the University of Washington, which wasnt originally on the itinerary. That unexpected stop made our day extra special.

The only downsideand the reason Im leaving a mixed reviewis what felt like a bait-and-switch when it came to an unexpected service fee. The night before our tour, I received a text from the guide letting me know there would be a $15 per person service fee, payable in cash. When I asked what it was for, there wasnt a clear explanation, which made it feel more like a mandatory tip than an actual service fee.

We always plan to tip for good service when we travel, and we absolutely intended to show our appreciation to our guide. However, being told how much to tip and being asked for it in cash (in addition to any optional gratuity) felt unprofessional and misleading. It left a sour taste on what was otherwise a great experience.

If the company is going to charge an extra fee, it should be clearly communicated upfront at the time of bookingnot sprung on guests at the last minute.

name: Seattle Cemetery Tour
description: Seattle's Original Cemetery tour takes you through a beautiful and historic cemetery. It is the site of the most ornate and interesting memorial monuments in the city. Every headstone tells a story, and every person buried there lived a life full of hopes and dreams, victories and defeats.

review.name: Excellent tour, excellent guide.
review.reviewBody: A great experience of the oldest Seattle cemetery tour, with full of historical knowledge, plus Black Sun sculpture, and the statue of William H. Seward in Volunteer Park.

review.name: Cool tour! Seattle History and Bruce Lee!
review.reviewBody: A cemetery tour might seem like a weird thing to do, but I have done them in New Orleans and Britain, and had a really great time. When I saw there was one in Seattle I booked it on their website right away. There are a lot of older style headstones in this beautiful old cemetery. Most of the Seattle pioneers are buried there along with Bruce Lee and his son Brandon. Our guide Joe was great. He was serious and hilarious during different times depending on what story he was telling.
